{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix resource block allocation in vendor extension callbacks\n\n### Summary\nThe vendor extension callback functions were not setting the phy_id in start request headers, causing incorrect resource block allocation downstream that violates scheduling constraints.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_vnf.c`: Added phy_id initialization in both LTE and NR vendor extension callback functions to ensure proper resource block allocation\n\n### Reproduction\nWithout this fix, when a vendor extension response is received and triggers a start request, the missing phy_id causes the scheduler to allocate resources incorrectly, leading to:\n- Segmentation faults in downstream PHY processing\n- Incorrect RB allocation that violates scheduling constraints\n- Failure to properly initialize the physical layer instance\n\nThe issue can be observed when running OAI with vendor extensions enabled and monitoring the resource allocation logs which will show invalid or conflicting RB assignments.\n"
}